text: The Digital Transformation Agency (DTA) is an Australian Federal Government agency formed on , succeeding the previous Digital Transformation Office. The agency has the stated goal of overseeing the "Digital Transformation Strategy" for the Australian Government to become "one of the leading digital governments in the world by 2025". Generally the agency oversees various interdepartmental government projects and provides consultancy and products to other official bodies. Notable projects of the DTA include myGov, Coronavirus Australia, and a CloudFoundry based cloud computing platform named cloud.gov.au. Additionally the DTA, in conjunction with Services Australia, is developing a myGov replacement currently titled "Government Digital Experience Platform" (GOVDXP). == References == Category:Government agencies established in 2016 Category:2016 establishments in Australia Category:Commonwealth Government agencies of Australia
